ms I need a new book based on Python 3.',66,'2011-08-16 00:31:18','2011-08-16 00:31:18',15),(158,'I really can not understand  how to work with this website,..',67,'2011-08-20 11:23:15','2011-08-20 11:23:15',2),(159,'Sure, when using ubuntu, we use `alt-ctrl-f1` and `alt-ctrl-f7` to switch among a console and GUI.\r\n\r\nHowever, if the ubuntu is installed as a VM machine, this sometimes does not work. I\'ve experienced this myself several times.\r\n\r\nI am not sure about this, but it seems that if you use `Window-alt-ctrl-f1` it might work. Try this out, and this is the only solution I know.\r\n\r\nAnybody has some idea?',68,'2011-08-23 08:38:43','2011-08-23 08:42:41',1),(160,'我也不会啊，哈哈。有人会吗？帮帮忙吧。\r\n\r\n我的意见是，不要花太多时间调这些东西，我自己以前吧大部分时间都用来调这些底层的问题，其实感觉调出来了也没学会太多东西。初学者在动手的时候应该专注自己的一个小领域，不要太宽；但同时学习和打基础要全面，不要太窄，同时也不要太难。\r\n\r\n不过要是真的急用某个东西，不调也不行啊，哈哈',69,'2011-08-24 02:12:52','2011-08-24 02:12:52',1),(161,'Check the following file:\r\n\r\nhttp://ubuntuguide.net/ubuntu-10-10-fix-the-screen-messed-up-at-start-up-and-shutdown\r\n\r\nWhen I used ThinkPad (E40) , there was no /dev/fb0 in my Ubuntu 10.10 system, but I needed to debug code involving frame buffer. After I googled lots of time, I found the file above, so I tried the method. Luckily, the file /dev/fb0 appeared, and when I restarted Ubuntu, it didn\'t mess up at the beginning, instead with beautiful screen. \r\n\r\nBy the way, my laptop used ATI display card. I didn\'t know why the problem could be fixed. It seemed like the problem had relation with Nvidia display driver. I was lucky!\r\n\r\nNow I recommend this article, it may help you.',69,'2011-08-24 03:16:46','2011-08-24 03:34:59',3),(162,'硕士毕业答辩，有这么简单吗？',70,'2011-08-24 09:32:57','2011-08-24 09:32:57',46),(163,'looking',70,'2011-08-24 12:23:51','2011-08-24 12:23:51',21),(164,'大家百度一下：\r\n\r\n    杜子华 英语成功学\r\n\r\n就可以开始骂我剽窃了，哈哈。\r\n\r\n实际我确实是买了一本书叫《杜子华英语成功学》，不过已经是我上本科那会儿的事情了。多年以后我还是很喜欢里面的方法，所以尽管多年没看那本书了，“剽窃”起来照样很溜儿⋯⋯',6,'2011-08-25 02:28:45','2011-08-25 02:32:50',1),(165,'我在这里也说了学习英语的“简单原则”\r\n\r\nhttp://www.happypeter.org/posts/6',72,'2011-08-25 02:37:21','2011-08-25 02:37:21',1),(166,'越简单越好（俞敏洪） \r\n\r\nhttp://www.happypeter.org/posts/72',6,'2011-08-25 02:37:54','2011-08-25 02:37:54',1),(167,'ubuntu totem (when plugin for mov installed) works like a charm',73,'2011-08-25 13:51:37','2011-08-25 13:51:37',1),(168,'windows test passed',73,'2011-08-25 13:58:14','2011-08-25 13:58:14',1),(169,'我想找一个外国妞练英语 ',72,'2011-08-26 06:41:07','2011-08-26 06:41:07',44),(170,'我用ubuntu10.10曾经也遇到过这个情况,后来从网上搜了好多解决方法,结果每次开机只能进入终端，试了很多办法也不能返回图形界面了，后来只能又换回9.04了。求完全解决方案',69,'2011-08-26 08:00:42','2011-08-26 08:00:42',7),(171,'@navyzhou\r\n\r\n你那个情况是在你机器的硬件上负责图形界面的程序（x server)起不来，我自己以前的旧机器上可以起来，起来后用一会儿就死机。\r\n\r\n这些问题有的可以解决，有的就只能换系统版本了，没有很好的解决方法。',69,'2011-08-26 13:42:04','2011-08-26 13:42:04',1),(172,'LS,你去劫一个呀，哈哈',72,'2011-08-29 01:58:10','2011-08-29 01:58:10',5),(174,'OK, I see what you mean, you want to display the code on the page, but you don\'t want to copy the code to the .md file, and you love to keep the .c file separate. Right?\r\n\r\nIf you are running your own server, this is actaully very easy to accomplish, simply by writing a little script to do exactly what you want. But as to github page, it is backed by [jekyll](https://github.com/mojombo/jekyll/wiki), so you only have what it offers, and nothing more. \r\n\r\nI do not think you can do this in jekyll. And I actully googled \"html include another file\", did not find any simple solution. \r\n\r\nAnyway, your problem now is that you are writing a tutorial, want to share some demo code snippets with your audience. This is just what [gist](https://gist.github.com/) is designed for. Check this\r\n\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/171713\r\n\r\nand if you add this single line in your .md file\r\n\r\n    <script src=\"https://gist.github.com/171713.js\"> </script>\r\n\r\n\r\nthe final result will be\r\n\r\nhttp://happypeter.github.com/GitBeijing/gist.html',74,'2011-08-29 13:48:57','2011-08-29 13:54:33',1);
