INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1,'Hi everybody','I use this site to communicate with people. \r\n\r\n - with written words, so that we can practice our writing, and we can talk about anything on each \'ticket\' we create\r\n\r\n - we do not use Email, we want other people to see what we are talking, and hopefully they get interested and join us.\r\n\r\n - free as in air','2011-06-29 02:24:47','2011-06-29 02:25:24',1),(2,'sign up','Cool! I\'m the second user on this site, except the site creator. I like this site for its simple style. The most important thing is it supports __Markdown__, which I use everyday.','2011-07-01 08:39:42','2011-07-01 08:41:01',3),(3,'feature request:  automatically login after signed up','I think the site has a small problem. After I signed up, it only tells me you have signed up successfully, but I can do nothing unless you log in using your account. This is not friendly. I think I should log in automatically after I signed up the first time. So can you modify this problem?','2011-07-01 09:59:13','2011-07-01 10:03:20',3),(4,'T-SHIRT','As we\'ve talked today, many of you want a shirt like mine(with happypeter.org on the back)\r\n\r\nSo plz post here, and let me know your size, options are\r\n\r\n - M\r\n - L\r\n - XL\r\n - XXL\r\n\r\n...','2011-07-02 13:17:46','2011-07-02 13:17:46',1),(5,'Letter to Song Jinshan','My dear Mr Song,\r\n\r\nI just finished your lecture on Software Development Process. I really like it.\r\n\r\n  But I do not really like the idea, you know what I care about management, I don\'t want to make it a serious science. I still love to stress on the human side: honor of developers as individuals. Team leader shall give his men some ego boost from time to time, all teams shall have pretty girl dev ...\r\n\r\nI really love\r\n\r\nhttp://gettingreal.37signals.com/ch01_What_is_Getting_Real.php\r\n\r\nThese days I am learning ROR.\r\n\r\nhttp://happypeter.github.com/ruby-on-rails.html\r\n\r\nand building my own\r\n\r\nwww.happypeter.org\r\n\r\nFirebug is a big help.( you showed me this when I was working under you, big thanks).  I am sure I am going to write some Unit test code soon, ROR people also love TDD and agile. The part on UnitTest in this lecture really helps.\r\n\r\n\r\nBTW. I mirrored your article here:\r\n\r\nhttp://happypeter.github.com/on-english-and-prog.html\r\n\r\nSo I think I need your permission. What would you say?\r\n\r\n\r\nwww.happypeter.org is build as a platform, where young students can ask anything they are interested in,(be it tech, career...) and hopefully some experienced dev will come and answer. It is definitely non-commercial. So I will be more than honored if you can join us, and post some articles for the students. All data will have triple-backup. So your post will be kept forever. We will later add some tagging and pointing system, so that good posts will not be buried by noise...\r\n\r\nHope some day, we can make a face-to-face, there are always so much I need to learn from you. Seriously!\r\n\r\n\r\n','2011-07-02 15:46:12','2011-08-28 15:24:43',1),(6,'音频-关于英语学习','大家好，这是我在长春上课时的课堂录音\r\n\r\n[mp3](http://media.happypeter.org/happycasts/happycity/changchun-casts/english.mp3)\r\n\r\n内容包括：\r\n\r\n - 简单原则,滚雪球式学习\r\n - 不学语法不考试原则\r\n - 投资提高兴趣','2011-07-03 14:16:21','2011-07-04 07:22:11',1),(7,'致所有想拜我为师的朋友','今天有同学给我来信，说要拜我为师，which really made my day!\r\n\r\nPeter本人阅历尚浅，根本没有实力给人当师傅。不过确实学LINUX 的人拜个师傅挺好的，我是2007年初拜的师，我师傅给我的帮助很大，我一直都非常感激她（注意是“她”）\r\n\r\n我是那种虚荣心很强的人，所以即使水平不够也很愿意多给人家讲职业和技术发展方面的事情。\r\n\r\n想拜我为师的人可以这样：\r\n\r\n - 给我买个礼物，10块钱以下的就行，例如钥匙缀\r\n - 关注 www.happypeter.org 上的新贴\r\n - 我们定期见面，我请你吃饭\r\n\r\n\r\n君子以文会友。\r\n','2011-07-04 14:04:28','2011-07-04 14:06:12',1),(8,'apt-get不能用了','执行sudo apt-get update的时候：\r\n\r\n忽略 http://extras.ubuntu.com maverick InRelease                               \r\n忽略 http://debian.nctu.edu.tw maverick InRelease                              \r\n忽略 http://archive.canonical.com maverick InRelease                     \r\n错误 http://archive.canonical.com maverick Release.gpg                         \r\n  解析“archive.canonical.com:http”时，出现了某些故障(-5 - 没有与主机名关联的地址)\r\n忽略 http://debian.nctu.edu.tw maverick-updates InRelease                      \r\n\r\n.............\r\n\r\n用sudo apt-get install 安装下载的时候也是这样的。\r\n求教是怎么回事？','2011-07-06 01:29:38','2011-07-06 01:29:38',8),(9,'May be a Bug ！','发帖后，帖子显示的时间不是北京时间！peter ，这是特意设置的还是Bug呢？','2011-07-06 02:23:36','2011-07-06 02:23:36',11),(10,'42期授课笔记','## tar \r\n\r\n关于压缩和解压，以下几种情况最常见:\r\n\r\n1.将名为`dir`的文件夹压缩为 `.tar.gz`的包：\r\n\r\n    tar zcvf  dir.tar.gz dir\r\n\r\n相应的解压命令：\r\n\r\n    tar zxvf dir.tar.gz \r\n\r\n2.将名为`dir`的文件夹压缩为 `.tar.bz2`的包：\r\n\r\n    tar jcvf dir.tar.bz2 dir\r\n\r\n相应的解压命令：\r\n\r\n    tar jxvf dir.tar.bz2\r\n\r\n当然以上过程也个以用**tar**, **bunzip2**, **gunzip**, 分别分为多步完成，但是一般不用，太麻烦，所以也不用记。以上的压缩方式，实际中只需记住一种就够用了，但是解压方式两种都要死记硬背下来，因为太常用了。\r\n\r\n## 扩展阅读\r\n\r\n\r\nhttp://happypeter.github.com/on-english-and-prog.html','2011-07-07 14:48:59','2011-07-07 15:26:54',1),(11,'周一来上课吧？','T-Shirt做好了吗？','2011-07-08 06:17:52','2011-07-08 06:17:52',5),(12,'hello peter   ','it\'s me zhaodsh \r\nthe site is very cool. so  I  decide to make one ,  but have other styles..... \r\nmay I write some  blogs  on this ?','2011-07-08 13:29:07','2011-07-08 13:30:07',16),(13,'code share-- search for a certain string with in a dir','### we have a simple request:\r\n\r\nthere is a directory with lots of subdirectory and files inside., now I want to know which files inside this tree contains a string \"foo\", I want to issue a command\"\r\n\r\n    xxx foo\r\n\r\nthe output should tell me which files contains the word \"foo\", print out all the lines with \"foo\". \r\n\r\nTo make things nicer, I can quickly select any match I want, and quickly open and edit it in vim.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### now I have two solutions:\r\n\r\nthe first is done with \r\n[shell script](https://github.com/happypeter/hen/blob/master/search/xxx)\r\nit is relatively simple, but the output is a bit ugly\r\n\r\nthe second is written in\r\n[C](https://github.com/happypeter/hen/blob/master/search/curse/xxx.c)\r\nit takes more code, but runs better\r\ncheck [how to install](https://github.com/happypeter/hen/blob/master/search/curse/wiki) \r\n','2011-07-08 14:32:41','2011-07-08 14:35:02',1),(14,'Hi Peter','It is very pretty cool here. ','2011-07-08 15:07:19','2011-07-08 15:07:19',18),(15,'http://www.linfo.org/','Do we know\r\n\r\n - what is a [command](http://www.linfo.org/command.html)?\r\n - what is [data](http://www.linfo.org/data.html)?\r\n\r\n\r\nEvery time I came to http://www.linfo.org/ , I was shocked by its beauty of simplicity. \r\n\r\n - easy English here that makes reading the text joyful experience\r\n - important concepts explained in a really nice and clear way\r\n','2011-07-08 15:25:08','2011-07-08 15:26:26',1),(16,'Build your own website','A lot of people want a personal website to share their stuff, Here are some of the options I\'ve tried over the years.\r\n\r\n### NO.1 Get a account from a blog hosting website\r\n\r\n__Examples:__ http://blog.chinaunix.net/space.php?uid=20653980\r\n\r\n__Pros:__ you don\'t need to build your site with java or PHP by hand, all the basic features are ready there for you. google and baidu usually favor these sites over your own site\r\n\r\n__Cons:__ there is little you can do if you want to do customization. You can change the theme and color a bit, but you can not add any new feature. I had really hard time trying to backup all my work on chinaunix.net, I need to do Copy&Paste by hand, that sucks!! \r\n\r\n\r\n__advice:__ I\'ve seen a lot of the programmers use http://wordpress.com/, it looks nice. I am annoyed many times by  http://blog.chinaunix.net, that\'s why I gave it up.\r\n\r\n### NO.2 use github pages\r\n\r\n__Examples:__ http://happypeter.github.com/   and  http://tom.preston-werner.com/\r\n\r\n__Pros:__ still you don\'t need to build your site with java or PHP by hand, you have total control over the look of your site, you can [blog like a hacker]( http://tom.preston-werner.com/2008/11/17/blogging-like-a-hacker.html), you can write in Markdown, and [jekyll](http://jekyllrb.com/) will translate it into html. All your data is in a gitrepo, data backup and synchronization can not be easier. \r\n\r\n__Cons:__ you need to learn Markdown and jekyll, and spend some time doing customization. The final result is still a STATIC page, you can not run any CGI script, I mean static is static.\r\n\r\n\r\n__advice:__ I love it so much, it runs really well, changing stuff and doing backup is so easy with the help of git and jeykll.\r\n\r\n## NO.3 a SF page\r\n\r\n__Examples:__ http://happypeter.users.sourceforge.net/\r\n\r\n__Pros:__ you have a basic LAMP environment. that means you can run CGI, you can code some PHP, and there is a lot more you can do I am sure, there is not hard quota, and still it it totally free. \r\n\r\n__Cons:__ I need rsync to backup my data (NOT git), I need to write a lot of the html( NOT Markdown), which is annoying to me, but still acceptable. The sucker that really drived me away from sf.net is really the performance, you have ssh, but you have little permission, and everything is so slow. \r\n\r\n\r\n__advice:__ It\'s still intersting if you want to try site-building and don\'t want spend any money. OR, if you have, say 1000RMB/year, I will suggest a VPS.\r\n\r\n## NO.4 a real server with real hardware\r\n\r\n__Examples:__ www.happypeter.org\r\n\r\n__Pros:__ you have everything you want!!!\r\n\r\n__Cons:__ It is so expensive!!! I spend more than 10000RMB/Year. \r\n\r\n\r\n__advice:__ Only needed when you really want to do something serious. \r\n\r\n','2011-07-09 03:09:17','2011-07-09 03:22:11',1),(17,'Hi everyone.I have changed my telephone number to 18611476526.','please reserve it to your contacts.\r\ngaojinlong','2011-07-10 13:17:26','2011-07-10 13:17:26',5),(18,'Notice! who booked the T-shirt!','Please come to akaedu to take your T-shirt.\r\nPeter will be in Taiyua